<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910729-0065</DOCNO><DOCID>910729-0065.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Old Kent Financial Corp.:   Letter of Intent Is Signed   On Buying Hasten Bancorp</HL><DATE>07/29/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   OKEN</CO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>CENTRAL U.S. BANKS (BAC)ALL REGIONAL BANKS (BAR)ALL BANKS, BANKING NEWS AND ISSUES (BNK)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>INDIANA (IND)MICHIGAN (MI)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Old Kent Financial Corp., Grand Rapids, Mich., said it hassigned a letter of intent to acquire Hasten Bancorp, a $600million, multibank holding company based in Indianapolis.   Hasten Bancorp stockholders will receive about $32.6million in cash and $34 million in preferred stock, for atotal purchase price of $66.6 million. The preferred willhave a dividend rate of 7.75% and be convertible into OldKent common stock at $34.85 a share. The affiliation issubject to the execution of a definitive agreement andapproval of state and federal regulatory agencies.</LP><TEXT>   Hasten Bancorp has four banks with 24 banking officeswithin a 100-mile radius of Indianapolis. Old Kent is a bankholding company with total assets of $8.3 billion.   Old Kent stock closed at $29.25, unchanged, in nationalover-the-counter trading Friday.</TEXT></DOC>